result.name: Amoy Plaza

reviews.text: Old private estate shopping mall struggling to compete with new ones.  It is not the new huge malls with high ceilings big brands but you may like the surprises and the rare shops at the corners or far end of corridors.  There are a few shops selling expert model kits for adults and toys for teenagers and game console games also.
Many good restaurants, many hobby stores. Something for everyone. Best of all, affordable price.
Many delicious food such as Genki Sushi and Pizza Hut

A lot of choices to choose from, a cinema and stuff like that. What you would hope from a decent shopping mall. There are also housing estates above the shopping centre but ofc it's too expensive for a normal human being in Hong Kong to afford
